  "$comment": "Slice 069 — per-package Go line-coverage floors enforced by cmd/scripts/coverage-gate.",
  "$methodology": "Floors are derived from a measured `go test -cover ./...` run on main (the CI `Go · build + test` job, unit-only, no integration tag). Each floor is set at `max(0, floor(measured - 2pp))` — the floor RATCHETS the current actual minus a 2-pp noise band, never reaches above it (slice 069 P0-A4).",
  "$how_to_raise": "Raise a per-package floor in a follow-up slice that (a) writes the additional tests to actually hit the new bar, (b) lifts the number here in the same PR. Do NOT raise floors in a slice that does not also write the tests.",
  "$how_to_extend": "When a new package lands, add a row here in the same PR. Default floor is the same `floor(measured - 2pp)` calculation. If a package is intentionally untested (sqlc-generated, protoc-generated, integration-tested elsewhere), add it to `excludes` instead.",
  "$schema_version": 1,

